# Operators · Interlace — non-V₄ inner-trigram projection placeholder

The `interlace` operator (互, 互卦) extracts an inner hexagram from
yao positions 2-3-4 and 3-4-5.  It is NOT a V₄ element — its only
fixed points are the all-yang and all-yin hexagrams, and the
`jiji ↔ weiji` pair is a 2-cycle.

The full definition with Yi naming lives in
`Foundation/Atlas/Yi/Operators.lean` (`Hexagram.hu`).  This file
remains as a placeholder for the R-index umbrella and does not
re-export anything from the legacy Yi/Bagua stack.
-/
